### Register DIRECTOR Maria
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "maria2@bright.com", "password": "password123", "displayName": "Maria" }

> {% client.global.set("mariaToken", response.body.token); %}

### Register TUTOR Tom
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "tom2@bright.com", "password": "password123", "displayName": "Tom" }

> {% client.global.set("tomToken", response.body.token); %}

### Register Bob (will own a different academy)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "bob2@smart.com", "password": "password123", "displayName": "Bob" }

> {% client.global.set("bobToken", response.body.token); %}

### Maria creates Academy A — she becomes its DIRECTOR
POST http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}

{ "name": "Bright Minds", "slug": "bright-minds-2" }

> {% client.global.set("academyA", response.body.id); %}

### Bob creates Academy B
POST http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{bobToken}}

{ "name": "Smart Scholars", "slug": "smart-scholars-2" }

> {% client.global.set("academyB", response.body.id); %}

### Maria adds Tom to Academy A as a TUTOR  -> 201
POST http://localhost:8080/api/members
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "email": "tom2@bright.com", "role": "TUTOR" }

### Maria creates a course in Academy A  -> 201
POST http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "title": "SAT Math", "subject": "Mathematics", "term": "Fall 2026" }

> {% client.global.set("courseA", response.body.id); %}

### Tom (TUTOR) reads courses in Academy A  -> 200
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{tomToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

### Tom (TUTOR) creates a course  -> 201 (TUTOR may manage courses)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tomToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "title": "SAT Verbal", "subject": "English", "term": "Fall 2026" }

### Tom (TUTOR) tries to add a member  -> 403 (only DIRECTOR/COORDINATOR may)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/members
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{tomToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyA}}

{ "email": "bob@smart.com", "role": "STUDENT" }

### CROSS-TENANT: Maria reads Academy B (not a member)  -> 403
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyB}}

### CROSS-TENANT: Bob (member of B) reads Academy A's course by id  -> 404
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses/{{courseA}}
Authorization: Bearer {{bobToken}}
X-Academy-Id: {{academyB}}

### Tenant endpoint with NO academy header  -> 403 (no academy role granted)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/courses
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}

### Maria lists her academies  -> only Academy A
GET http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Authorization: Bearer {{mariaToken}}